&lt;p&gt;Help craft the online experience for top-tier B2B SaaS companies — and set a higher standard for modern marketing websites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our website is our most important marketing asset — where pipeline starts, brand is formed, and every campaign dollar lands. We need a web architect who sets our technical direction rather than taking tickets: an elite engineering mind who understands that code is a lever for revenue. You’ll work on a stack built on Astro.js, TypeScript, and Sanity, integrated with HubSpot, GTM, Google Analytics, Intercom, and Zendesk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the systems architecture for our marketing website — authoritative decisions on platform, stack, infrastructure, and performance, with daily hands-on work in the codebase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design the technical foundation for experimentation at scale: A/B testing frameworks, personalisation middleware, and rapid iteration pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect the Sanity content infrastructure for a “Create Once, Publish Everywhere” workflow, including content models, reusable blocks, and ingestion pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the website data layer, event architecture, and tracking standards; monitor and optimize Core Web Vitals, uptime, and technical SEO/AI visibility continuously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prototype and deploy AI-driven features — personalisation, dynamic content, intelligent search — with AI tooling as a default part of your workflow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical oversight of external agencies and contractors: enforcing PR standards, CI/CD pipelines, and ensuring output meets our architectural bar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring data-backed recommendations to senior stakeholders, mentor colleagues, and raise the bar for web engineering across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position is for you if you have…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of web development experience, with at least 5 years at senior or principal level in B2B SaaS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical Astro.js and Sanity experience; Next.js/TypeScript backgrounds considered with strong Sanity proficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of guiding major web projects end-to-end — architecture through launch — with rigorous engineering workflows: version control, PR reviews, deployment pipelines, and incident management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing experimentation and personalisation platforms: A/B testing systems, dynamic content delivery, and scalable growth architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical SEO and AI visibility knowledge at the systems level, plus deep analytics and tracking experience across GTM, event architecture, and platforms like HubSpot, Marketo, and Segment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Daily use of AI development tools (Cursor, GitHub Copilot, Claude, etc.) and a track record of shipping AI-driven site features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to communicate technical trade-offs clearly to non-technical stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits we offer…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation package, including equity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great work equipment and home office allowance for remote locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health care benefit and leisure time insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;€1,000 annual personal learning budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sports and wellbeing allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-HYBRID&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
