&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Global Workplace Experience Specialist who is as comfortable building AI-driven processes for facilities management as they are organising a great company event. Based in our Helsinki HQ, you&#39;ll play an active role in shaping the workplace environment, global compliance, and the key culture moments that connect us, using smart tools and automation to do it better, faster, and at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll identify and implement AI-driven solutions that improve how the office runs, how new joiners are welcomed, and how employees experience Supermetrics day to day. If you&#39;re motivated by reimagining traditional workplace processes through the lens of modern tech, data, and compliance, this role was built for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own onboarding and offboarding experience end-to-end, blending AI-driven automation with a personal touch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee employee engagement and culture programming throughout our global offices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own workplace compliance and Health &amp;amp; Safety standards globally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage day-to-day workplace operations and digital space management for Helsinki and our global offices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your day-to-day work and responsibilities include…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver a personalised onboarding experience for every new hire, from welcome packages and office introductions to first-week orientation, using AI to automate and personalise communications and checklists without losing the human touch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve onboarding using survey data and feedback, partnering closely with People Ops for a seamless handoff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own all Slack communications and automated comms flows related to workplace experience, office updates, events, and culture moments, so nothing falls through the cracks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and run an annual events plan for global locations, celebrating country-specific cultural events and holidays, and coordinate company events, team celebrations, and cultural initiatives across our global footprint&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI to automate end-to-end event logistics, including vendor procurement and budget management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement a &quot;Culture Map&quot; plan for Supermetrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate global Health &amp;amp; Safety initiatives and own workplace compliance across all office locations, using smart systems to track mandatory training, fire audits, and emergency protocols in line with local regulatory standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop scalable guidelines and playbooks that help all Supermetrics offices maintain a consistent, high-quality, compliant experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the day-to-day running of the Helsinki and global offices, including vendor management, facilities coordination, and budget tracking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deploy and analyse digital floor mapping and occupancy sensor data, translating it into insights that optimise office layouts and inform future real estate decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build AI-driven workflows for predictive maintenance, smart desk configuration, and automated procurement, and deploy an AI-powered chatbot to handle employee facility requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position is for you if you have/are…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years in employee experience, workplace operations, people operations, or a closely related role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical experience building or implementing AI-driven processes — you&#39;ve deployed AI tools (e.g., Claude, chatbot builders) to solve real problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with managing and supporting Health &amp;amp; Safety protocols and workplace compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A people-first a

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Play a key role in managing the financial operations of a fast-scaling global tech company.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Supermetrics, we&#39;re on a mission to make data easier for everyone. Now, we&#39;re looking for an experienced and motivated &lt;strong&gt;Group Financial Controller&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Finance team in our Helsinki HQ.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a key role for someone ready to manage group-level financial operations in an agile and international SaaS environment. If you&#39;re practical, detail-oriented, and motivated to grow with a global team, this could be your next big career move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for monthly and year-end close procedures including preparation of journal entries and balance sheet reconciliations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and analyse financial statements, management reports, and other key financial documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct in-depth financial analysis and provide recommendations to improve financial performance and control across the Group.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to day-to-day financial operations including AR, AP, Procurement, Expenses, Treasury and Payroll.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to and maintain group, parent and subsidiary tax compliance, including direct and indirect taxation, transfer pricing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain robust internal controls to ensure compliance with internal policies, accounting standards and local regulations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage external audit during annual Group and statutory audits and assist in resolving audit queries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare local financial statements in Finland&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continually evaluate and optimise monthly close and other finance processes, striving to deliver best practice in process automation, efficiencies and improved accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s/Master&#39;s degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical accounting and tax knowledge (international and local GAAP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 3-4 years experience, gained in a multinational technology business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with NetSuite or other ERP tools such as Oracle, SAP, and Workday.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively in a deadline-driven environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to haves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building agentic workflows or process automation using AI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with close management tools such as FloQast or Stacks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attractive pay and benefits, including equity participation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great work equipment, and home office allowance for those working in our fully remote locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health care benefit and leisure time insurance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual €1,000 personal learning budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sports and wellbeing allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
